The Anti-Duterte ad though obviously a blunt form of negative propaganda is 
unfortunately legal under Republic Act 9006 known as the Fair Elections Act 
as clearly defined by Section 1a of Comelec Resolution 3636 which allows 
the campaign for or against any candidate. I reviewed the ad myself and its 
very unfortunate that we cannot stop the use actual clips of Duterte's 
indiscretions even if he already apologized for them. In compliance to 
MTRCB rules, his cursing and dirty finger was edited out. As for the use of 
children, they were simply portrayed to be asking questions on common moral 
values and were not in any manner portrayed to be a victim or perhaps 
favoring abuse, exploitation or anything immoral. However, my question is: 
WHO PAID FOR THIS AD? Section 4.1 of the Fair Elections Act explicitly 
requires the legible announcement of who paid for the ad and to whose 
benefit at the end of each ad.﻿
